Header.title: ECE Outreach
Header.paragraph: Students of Colorado State University bringing passion for Electrical and Computer Engineering to students from middle school to college.

About.paragraph: ECE Outreach is devoted to making Electrical and Computer Engineering more accessible to students by delivering it in small, exciting, and informative packages. Our team works to develop exciting workshops and inspiring demonstrations, opening up the world of electronics to students who may never have considered this exciting path for their education and career.

Team.name: Kailee Mitsuyasu
Team.description: Hi my name is Kailee. Professionally, I am interested in VLSI, circuit design, and embedded systems. In my spare time I love to cook and play the guitar.

Team.name: Brandon Crisp
Team.description: I‚Äôm a senior in Electrical Engineering, and lead of the Analog Outreach Team, and I‚Äôm interested in power electronics.

Team.name: Ian Johnson
Team.description: I have been a part of the CSU ECE Outreach team for a little over a year and have worked on several projects in that time. I am a firm believer in reducing carbon emissions by biking and home cooked meals.

Team.name: Cole Taylor
Team.description: I am a senior in Electrical Engineering, the Controls team lead of the Rocket Team at CSU, and have a passion for aerospace and automotives.

Team.name: Ryan Barnes
Team.description: I am a senior in Electrical Engineering and am the current ECE Outreach Team Lead. I am interested in signal processing, specifically in the field of biomedical imaging and sensing.

Team.name: David Neitenbach
Team.description: I really enjoy climbing and playing hockey! These let me clear my head and relax. I also really like to design and build speakers in my free time. It isn't the cheapest hobby but I really enjoy it!

Team.name: Devin Pohl

Team.name: Jacklyn Moore
Team.description: I am a junior in both Electrical Engineering & Biomedical Engineering. I am part of the Math Team in ECE Outreach, and I am interested in pursuing a career in cardiology!

Team.name: Kendra Ott
Team.description: I'm a Junior in Computer Engineering and I lead the math team. I love programming and am interested in firmware.

Team.name: Kori Eliaz
Team.description: I‚Äôm a junior in Electrical Engineering and lead of the Media team. I‚Äôm super passionate about all things aerospace, specifically deep space communications.

Team.name: TJ Dunham
Team.description: I‚Äôm an Electrical Engineering junior and lead for the EV3 Robotics team. I‚Äôm here because I believe outreach is one of the most important endeavors we can take on as engineering students.

Team.name: Vani Kapoor
Team.description: I am a Junior Electrical Engineering student. I have been a part of the outreach team since my sophomore year. I am interested in going into project management in the automotive industry.

Team.name: Ethan Schultz
Team.description: I am a sophomore majoring in Electrical Engineering. I really enjoy programming and working on side projects.

Team.name: Naser Moin
Team.description: I am a second year undergraduate in computer engineering. My interests include software and digital systems, and I also have a passion for teaching others.

Team.name: Thomas Balzer
Team.description: I am a freshman electrical engineering student interested in controls and robotics.

Team.name: Ticus Brandt
Team.description: I am a Freshman in Computer Engineering. I have a passion for inventing and innovating and using any chance to get creative.

Team.name: Pacen Whited
Team.description: I am a freshman computer engineering student and have an interest in software development and embedded systems.

Alumni.name: Jameson Richard
Alumni.quote: ECE opens up a world of potential, both for your career prospects and for your free time.

Alumni.name: Joseph Stubitz
Alumni.quote: ECE majors help keep the lights on and are powering us toward the future.

Alumni.name: Jarvis Hill
Alumni.quote: Give 100% in the current moment; it will always lead to your next greatest moment; you‚Äôll never have to sit around wondering in a null state of life.

Alumni.name: Ian Bernstein
Alumni.quote: With sensors, microcontrollers, and computers surrounding us from our cars to our fitness equipment to sleep aids, ECE is becoming more and more important every day. Not to mention how fun, creative, and rewarding it can be!
